Number = {{1}},
Pages = {{1-31}},
Month = {{FEB}},
Abstract = {{We investigate the hypothesis of failed integration and low social
   mobility of immigrants. An intergenerational assimilation model is
   tested empirically on household survey data and validated against
   registry data provided by the Italian Embassy in Germany. Although we
   confirm substantial disparities between educational achievements of
   immigrants and natives, we find that the children of Italian immigrants
   exhibit high intergenerational mobility and no less opportunity than
   natives to achieve high schooling degrees. These findings suggest a
   rejection of the failed assimilation hypothesis. Additionally, we
   evaluate different patterns by time of arrival, Italian region of origin
   and language spoken at home.}},
